Package cp213

Class DoubleLink<T>

java.lang.Object
cp213.DoubleLink<T>
Type Parameters:
T - data type for base data structure.
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Iterable<T>
Direct Known Subclasses:
DoubleDeque, DoubleList, DoubleQueue, DoubleSortedList
public abstract class DoubleLink<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<T>
The abstract base class for doubly-linked data structures. Provides attributes and implementations for getLength, isEmpty, toArray, and iterator methods. The front attribute is the first node in any doubly-linked list and rear the last node.

2019-01-26

    • toArray

      public final T[] toArray()
      Returns an array of data from a deque. Not thread safe as it assumes contents of deque are not changed by an external thread during the copy loop. If data elements are added or removed by an external thread while the data is being copied to the array, then the declared array length may no longer be valid.
      Returns:
      an array of data of type T. Returns null if the deque is empty.
